## Flow Workflow

This project uses **Flow** — a spec-driven development workflow for AI agents.
Changes move through three states: **drafting** → **building** → **closed**.

Flow phase commands drive the workflow. The canonical phase names are shown below with slash-command syntax. Use `$flow-<name>` in Codex, `/flow-<name>` in Claude Code/Cursor, or `flow <name>` in a shell. `/flow-status` is read-only orientation:

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `/flow-start [description]` | Draft a new spec with inline clarifying questions |
| `/flow-amend [change request]` | Update the active `spec.md` without creating a new spec |
| `/flow-plan` | Draft the implementation plan and the task list (always emits `tasks.md`) |
| `/flow-build` | Implement all remaining tasks test-first; final task completion runs verification |
| `/flow-build-task [task]` | Implement one next or selected task test-first |
| `/flow-test` | Rerun verification: tests and consistency checks |
| `/flow-close` | Close a completed child change in place and update the parent run |
| `/flow-roadmap <source>` | Create a planned roadmap run with run-local milestones |
| `/flow-run [M-N]` | Automate the active roadmap run end-to-end — every open milestone, or one when `M-N` is given |
| `/flow-status` | Read-only: current state + consistency findings + next recommended action |

The installer `/flow-setup` runs once on first use of any other command.

## Key Files

- `flow/README.md` — Short map for Flow's visible workspace and hidden control plane
- `flow/runs/YYYYMMDD-<run-slug>/` — Run state, durable logs, owner manuals, release notes, and child changes
- `flow/runs/<run>/roadmap.md` — Run-local milestone roadmap (M-N items)
- `flow/runs/<run>/changes/<change>/` — Change artifacts (spec, plan, tasks, status)
- `flow/docs/` — Flow-maintained current documentation, unless configured otherwise
- `.flow/conventions/` — Flow-owned schema contract (sharded by phase); see `docs/reference/artifacts.md` for the human-readable version
- `.flow/config.yaml` — Project-scoped configuration (layout, visible prefix, confirmation, test command, phase effort)
- `.flow/state.yaml` — Flow-owned mutable state such as the roadmap counter
- `.flow/agents/<phase>.base.md` — Phase agent prompt bases (updated by `/flow-setup`)
- `.flow/agents/<phase>.local.md` — Your local overrides (never touched by Flow)
- `docs/principles.md` — Engineering Principles (optional; read live by every phase if present)
- `docs/decisions/` — Important technical decisions promoted at release time

## Conventions

Artifacts follow the schema contract described in `docs/reference/artifacts.md` and stored for Flow to read under `.flow/conventions/` (Flow-owned; do not edit by hand). Key rules:

- `spec.md` requires one section: `## What & Why`. Other sections are optional.
- `plan.md` requires three sections: `## Summary`, `## Technical Context`, `## Documentation Impact`.
- All IDs (`FR-NNN`, `SC-NNN`, `T-NNN`, `P-NNN`, `M-N`) are stable across edits.
- Section headings are identity — spelling must be exact.
- `status.md` is the single source of truth for state. Never edit it directly; Flow's scripts handle it atomically.

## Guard rails

- Flow never runs `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, `gh`, or `glab`.
- On protected branches (`main`, `master`, `trunk`, `develop`, `release/*`) Flow warns and prompts before proceeding. Set `FLOW_FORCE_ON_PROTECTED=1` to skip the prompt.
- Flow does not create tags, merges, pushes, pulls, fetches, or GitHub/GitLab operations. The only commit exceptions are local roadmap-run checkpoint commits and the run-closing commit created by `flow run --finalize`, both when `git.run_checkpoint_commits: true`.

